    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing TLV tag initialization in measurement request packing\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_measurement_request` function was not properly initializing TLV tags before attempting to pack measurement parameters. This caused the underlying `pack_tlv` calls to skip packing any measurement data because the tag comparison `tl->tag == tag` would fail when `tl->tag` was uninitialized (typically zero).\n\nThe issue manifested as missing measurement configuration in PNF parameter exchanges, causing incorrect RF power reporting. Under certain conditions with multiple measurement requests, this could lead to inconsistent power control behavior.\n\nThe root cause was that `pack_tlv` only packs data when the TLV's tag matches the expected tag, but the measurement request function was not setting these tags before calling `pack_tlv`.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Added explicit TLV tag initialization in `pack_measurement_request` for all three measurement parameters (DL RS TX power, received interference power, and thermal noise power) before calling `pack_tlv`.\n\n"
}